3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper evaluates the computational efficiency of the proposed mechanisms, which is a core concern in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the interaction between requesters and workers in crowdsourcing markets, which is a topic of interest in human-computer interaction. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper touches on the issue of fairness in crowdsourcing markets, which is a topic of concern in the intersection of computers and society.
